<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="65" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/674a:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-12T20:00:00-04:00">December 12, 1942—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6308. Department’s 6291, December 11, midnight. The Soviet
                                Ambassador<note n="52" xml:id="d65fn52">Maxim Maximovich
                                Litvinov.</note> has proposed the following amendment to the joint
                            declaration: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“After the sentence concerning the deliberate extermination of
                                    Jews by way of mass executions add: ‘The number of victims of
                                    these sanguinary punishments is taken to amount to many hundreds
                                    of thousands of quite innocent men, women and children’.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>This amendment is entirely satisfactory to the Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>